==English==

===Etymology===
Found as early as 1837, in ''Pickwick Papers'' by [[w:Charles Dickens|Charles Dickens]], where it appears in the form, “It’s a reg’lar holiday to them—all porter and skittles”. The most common form, as a negative admonition, appears to have been popularized by [[w:Thomas Hughes|Thomas Hughes]] in ''Tom Brown's School Days'' (1857, see quotation below).

